title: Black
overview: The cathartic tale of a young woman who can't see, hear or talk and the teacher who brings a ray of light into her dark world.

title: Philadelphia
overview: When a man with HIV is fired by his law firm because of his condition, he hires a homophobic small time lawyer as the only willing advocate for a wrongful dismissal suit.

title: American History X
overview: A former neo-nazi skinhead tries to prevent his younger brother from going down the same wrong path that he did.

title: Jagten
overview: A teacher lives a lonely life, all the while struggling over his son's custody. His life slowly gets better as he finds love and receives good news from his son, but his new luck is about to be brutally shattered by an innocent little lie.

title: Boyhood
overview: The life of Mason, from early childhood to his arrival at college.

title: Gifted
overview: Frank, a single man raising his child prodigy niece Mary, is drawn into a custody battle with his mother.

title: Udaan
overview: Expelled from his school, a 16-year old boy returns home to his abusive and oppressive father.

title: Vozvrashchenie
overview: In the Russian wilderness, two brothers face a range of new, conflicting emotions when their father - a man they know only through a single photograph - resurfaces.

title: Tumbbad
overview: A mythological story about a goddess who created the entire universe. The plot revolves around the consequences when humans build a temple for her first-born.

title: Hamlet
overview: Hamlet, Prince of Denmark, returns home to find his father murdered and his mother remarrying the murderer, his uncle. Meanwhile, war is brewing.

title: Network
overview: A television network cynically exploits a deranged former anchor's ravings and revelations about the news media for its own profit.

title: American Beauty
overview: A sexually frustrated suburban father has a mid-life crisis after becoming infatuated with his daughter's best friend.

title: Ondskan
overview: A teenage boy expelled from school for fighting arrives at a boarding school where the systematic bullying of younger students is encouraged as a means to maintain discipline, and decides to fight back.

title: Forushande
overview: While both participating in a production of "Death of a Salesman," a teacher's wife is assaulted in her new home, which leaves him determined to find the perpetrator over his wife's traumatized objections.

title: Room
overview: Held captive for 7 years in an enclosed space, a woman and her young son finally gain their freedom, allowing the boy to experience the outside world for the first time.

title: Detachment
overview: A substitute teacher who drifts from classroom to classroom finds a connection to the students and teachers during his latest assignment.

title: Mysterious Skin
overview: A teenage hustler and a young man obsessed with alien abductions cross paths, together discovering a horrible, liberating truth.

title: Hiroshima mon amour
overview: A French actress filming an anti-war film in Hiroshima has an affair with a married Japanese architect as they share their differing perspectives on war.

title: Smultronstället
overview: After living a life marked by coldness, an aging professor is forced to confront the emptiness of his existence.

title: Höstsonaten
overview: A married daughter who longs for her mother's love is visited by the latter, a successful concert pianist.
